#Some commands are ##

	- git config --list 

>> Should give the informatoin 

# Modify config 

	- git config --global user.name "Jeff Delaney"
       ` - git config --global user.email "hello@fireship.io"

## Some fundamentals ##

	- git commit -a -m "this is another commit"


## git remote ##
	- git remote add origin <link>
	- git remote 
	- git remote show 


## git push ##

	- git push origin master -u 

>> "-u" : set origin to upstream remote 

## This basically helps with git pull when getting things from the remote repo without any extra arguments ##

## Git Fetch & Merge ##

	- git fetch >> pulls the latest remote repo changes

	>> however, make sure to check the head of each remote and local master branch and see that the commits are different


## git merge ##

	- git merge origin/master 

>> This will essentially merge the local repo with the master and the head will be pointing to the same commit....

## git pull ##

>> git pull makes things easier, combines fetch and merge together.


	- git pull 

## git clone ##

>> cloning the remote repo 

	- git clone <url>

	- git log >> for the history of commits 


## git branch ##

	- git branch -b cool

>> let's me create and checkout to the branch